  "chapter": {
    "number": 52,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Deliverance for Jerusalem"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Awake, awake,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "clothe yourself with strength, O Zion!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Put on your garments of splendor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O Jerusalem, holy city!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For the uncircumcised and unclean",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will no longer enter you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shake off your dust!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Rise up and sit on your throne, O Jerusalem.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Remove the chains from your neck,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O captive Daughter of Zion.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "For this is what the LORD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“You were sold for nothing,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and without money you will be redeemed.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "For this is what the Lord GOD says:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“At first My people went down to Egypt to live,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "then Assyria oppressed them without cause.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And now what have I here?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For My people have been taken without cause;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "those who rule them taunt,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2689
          },
          {
            "text": "declares the LORD,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and My name is blasphemed continually",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "all day long.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2690
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore My people will know My name;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "therefore they will know on that day",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "that I am He who speaks.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Here I am!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "How beautiful on the mountains",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "are the feet of those who bring good news,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2691
          },
          {
            "text": "who proclaim peace, who bring good tidings,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who proclaim salvation,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who say to Zion, “Your God reigns!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Listen! Your watchmen lift up their voices,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "together they shout for joy.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For every eye will see",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when the LORD returns to Zion.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Break forth in joy, sing together,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O ruins of Jerusalem,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for the LORD has comforted His people;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He has redeemed Jerusalem.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD has bared His holy arm",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in the sight of all the nations;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "all the ends of the earth will see",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the salvation of our God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Depart, depart, go out from there!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Touch no unclean thing;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2692
          },
          {
            "text": "come out from it, purify yourselves,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you who carry the vessels of the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For you will not leave in a hurry",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor flee in haste,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for the LORD goes before you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the God of Israel is your rear guard.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Servant Exalted"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, My Servant will prosper;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2693
          },
          {
            "text": "He will be raised and lifted up and highly exalted.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Just as many were appalled at Him",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2694
          },
          {
            "text": "—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "His appearance was disfigured beyond that of any man,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and His form was marred beyond human likeness—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "so He will sprinkle",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2695
          },
          {
            "text": "many nations.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Kings will shut their mouths because of Him.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For they will see what they have not been told,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and they will understand what they have not heard.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2696
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
